  "doc_id": "59660",
  "text": "For an anomalous triggered lightning flash, Wang et al. [CITATION_1] found that the two return stroke current waves were initiated at a height of about 23 m above the strike object (at the junction point between the downward leader and upward connecting leader), and the initiation was associated with the beginning of the SF front. They have concluded that both the SF and FT \"start at the return stroke initiation height\". In our study, the heights of the downward leader tip at the time of CSZ onset could be estimated for 3 of the 4 events and ranged from 42 to 46 m, with the corresponding NLDN-reported peak currents ranging from 37 to 55 kA. For comparison, in two photoelectric studies of Wang et al. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] the return-stroke initiation heights for 4 first strokes were estimated to be 12 to 63 m, with the corresponding NLDN-reported peak currents being 8.9 to 76 kA.",
